{
  "stem": "13457.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So now we're starting a, a new segment in, in this saga of Second World War.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I would like to go backwards now into Warsaw into the broader aspects of what was happening before the war in Warsaw, even though I was nine years old at that time.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "What was happening at that time, that there was virulent anti-Semitism that was even clear to me at the time.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't know what was the occasion for the Poles, but I think that was the part at the time when the Germans walk-- walked into Czechoslovakia, and the Poles were very happy that happened.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Incidentally, that's when Poland took a piece of Czechoslovakia too.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were very happy.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the way they showed their happiness, they were throwing the Jews out of the windows in the university and beating up Jews on the streets.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] From what I remember, one of the friends, a doctor of my father, was brutalized.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Then there were pogroms, too.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There were pogroms with the Jewish self defense.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The Jewish porters, the shtarkers, organized themselves.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And from what I understand, my father was, was working with this sort of counter or self defense in the sense that when-- if these porters would be beaten up by the Endeks.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Endeks was a group of f-- rightist anti-Semitic movement in the university, and they were then beating up the Jews on the streets.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But the porters-- the Jewish porters-- apparently were also luring them into gates and beating the shit out of them also, so that maybe went both ways.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
